{
  "stem": "21139.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And one woman that-- one woman that lived near, very near to the synagogue, she wrapped the-- a piece of the Torah and took it in.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And my mother said to me and to my-- and to Siegie-- there was a family living on the first floor, a non-Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And she said to me, go get the keys.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Maybe we can go to their apartments to hide.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Well, I-- and she told me where to go.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Siegie and I-- I took him by the hand and we went together.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But I couldn't walk.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I-- the-- the shock from it all all was in my-- my legs.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I returned and I told my mother, I can't go.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I cannot walk.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So what she did, she took us into the garden [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was in-- it was November.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was cool already.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we-- the clothes we had, the warm clothes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she took us in the garden and we stayed there until it was night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Every once in a while, she said to me, go and look and see from the barn where the entrance is if you see something.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and I couldn't see anything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And for some reason, it's like a miracle, they never came to our house to destroy.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then when-- at night, we went back to the house.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Gestapo came several times looking for my father, because they wanted to take him also to Dachau or to one of those places.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we didn't-- for a few days, we didn't know what happened to my father, because he was in Pforzheim.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
